  "timeframe": "1H (bias) / 5m (entry)",
  "market_context": "ES took out the upside of the range on the 1-hour and closed back inside, establishing a bearish bias. Price then opened and dropped, reached back into a 1-hour fair value gap in premium and formed a candle 2 closure around 5955, setting up continuation lower toward -1, -2, and -2.5 standard deviation targets.",
  "key_observation": "After the candle 2 closure on the 1H in premium, the 5-minute provided multiple continuation entries where price retraced into fair value gaps, swept a short-term high, and closed through up-close candles, validating shorts toward lower targets.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Identified on the 1-hour that price had taken out the high side of the range and closed back inside, defining a bearish daily bias.",
    "Waited for structure to form rather than chasing the initial drop, looking for a lower high or retracement into a 1-hour fair value gap in premium.",
    "Marked the candle 2 closure on the 1H near 5955 after price reached back into the fair value gap, anticipating a reversal lower.",
    "Dropped to the 5-minute time frame to seek continuation entries aligned with the 1H bearish bias.",
    "Noted the initial 5m reversal was messy, so opted to skip catching the reversal and wait for a continuation setup.",
    "Took the first continuation entry when price retraced into an important level, swept a short-term high, and closed below the up-close candle(s), targeting the lows.",
    "Rejected a subsequent candle as a valid continuation because it did not reach into a fair value gap or sweep a high before closing lower.",
    "Identified a later continuation entry where price retraced into a qualifying fair value gap and closed through the up-close candles, taking the trade for a second attempt.",
    "Confirmed both qualifying continuation entries reached at least 2R toward the downside targets."
  ],
  "outcome": "Both qualifying continuation entries delivered at least 2R toward the downside targets.",
  "lessons": "When a candle 2 closure forms in premium on the HTF, multiple LTF continuation entries can be taken as long as each retracement reaches a fair value gap, sweeps a short-term high, and closes through the up-close candles. Strict mechanical criteria filter low-quality continuations.",
